annotationA: Probable nucleoporin Nup54; Probable component of the nuclear pore complex, a complex required for the trafficking across the nuclear membrane (By similarity). May have a role in the organization of the inner nuclear membrane proteins at the nuclear envelope together with Nup154; Belongs to the NUP54 family
annotationB: Hsc70Cb, isoform G; Hsc70Cb is an HSP110 family protein, and interacts physically with DnaJ-1 as a chaperone of misfolded proteins. Hsc70Cb functions together with DnaJ-1 to prevent the toxicity of aggregation-prone proteins
